questions.title: Reverse a String
questions.description: Write a function that reverses a string. The input string is given as an array of characters s. You must do this by modifying the input array in-place with O(1) extra memory.

questions.title: Linked List Cycle Detection
questions.description: Implement a function to detect if a linked list contains a cycle.

questions.title: Roman to Integer
questions.description: Given a roman numeral, convert it to an integer.

questions.title: Add Binary
questions.description: Given two binary strings a and b, return their sum as a binary string.

questions.title: Fibonacci Number
questions.description: The Fibonacci numbers form a sequence, called the Fibonacci sequence, such that each number is the sum of the two preceding ones. Given n, calculate F(n).

questions.title: Implement Stack using Queues
questions.description: Implement a last-in-first-out (LIFO) stack using only two queues. The implemented stack should support all the functions of a normal stack (push, top, pop, and empty).

questions.title: Combine Two Tables
questions.description: Write a solution to report the first name, last name, city, and state of each person in the Person table. If the address of a personId is not present in the Address table, report null instead.

questions.title: Repeated DNA Sequences
questions.description: Given a string s that represents a DNA sequence, return all the 10-letter-long sequences (substrings) that occur more than once in a DNA molecule.

questions.title: Course Schedule
questions.description: Return true if you can finish all courses. Otherwise, return false.

questions.title: LRU Cache Design
questions.description: Design and implement an LRU (Least Recently Used) cache.

questions.title: Longest Common Subsequence
questions.description: Given two strings, return the length of their longest common subsequence.

questions.title: Rotate Image
questions.description: Given an n x n 2D matrix representing an image, rotate the image by 90 degrees clockwise.

questions.title: Airplane Seat Assignment Probability
questions.description: Return the probability that the nth person gets their own seat.

questions.title: Validate Binary Search Tree
questions.description: Given the root of a binary tree, determine if it is a valid binary search tree (BST).

questions.title: Sliding Window Maximum
questions.description: Return the max sliding window for an array of integers.

questions.title: N-Queen Problem
questions.description: Given an integer n, return all distinct solutions to the n-queens puzzle.

questions.title: Serialize and Deserialize a Binary Tree
questions.description: Design an algorithm to serialize and deserialize a binary tree.

questions.title: Wildcard Matching
questions.description: Implement wildcard pattern matching with support for '?' and '*'.

questions.title: Chalkboard XOR Game
questions.description: Alice and Bob take turns erasing exactly one number from the chalkboard. Return true if and only if Alice wins the game, assuming both players play optimally.

questions.title: Trips and Users
questions.description: Write a solution to find the cancellation rate of requests with unbanned users each day.
